eport. There’s no instruction against editing metadata, but I see it suggests adding or refining tests to cover uncovered call sites. Adding metadata for the test helper class seems tricky since it's part of the library metadata, not the test package. I wonder if native configuration for test classes should be in the test resources. Is there a mechanism for this? I'll need to check the META-INF/native-image for test resources.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Rkq8bkeKAY0wXhRC9gjybO25|fc_091dce4811d4f3220169f523eabf6c8197b8337fef5e53e610", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src -path '*/META-INF/native-image/*' -type f | head -20", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1273, "output": 2220, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42405, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777673163916, "responseId": "resp_091dce4811d4f3220169f523cc5e8081979d59dd25a05c8a1f"}}
